column1: With Thanksgiving just a few days away I’m thankful for the incredible public health workers who are doing so much to keep us safe during COVID-19 — your work saves lives. #PHTYD

The #COVID19 crisis has been hard on our #ag community but there are programs available to help. I encourage farmers & producers in #MN06 to utilize resources like #CFAP & the Dairy Margin Coverage program from @USDA https://t.co/SW5VXoRWaB

#PrecisionMedicine is the future of medical innovation for everything from finding a cure for #cancer to creating targeted therapies to treat #COVID19. I was pleased to speak at the latest briefing of the #PersonalizedMedicine Caucus which I Co-Chair. https://t.co/JVxL7WTh8K
The #COVID19 crisis has revealed the struggles in improving #healthcare for our rural communities. This #NationalRuralHealthDay let’s focus on closing the gap. https://t.co/Nc3cAenODP

#Youthsports aren’t just an afterschool activity. They teach our kids social and leadership skills provide essential physical activity and give parents a much-needed break during this #COVID19 crisis. #Unite2PLAY
Nursing homes & assisted living facilities have been suffering during the #COVID19 crisis — & with insufficient govt support #seniors suffer esp in our rural communities. https://t.co/0rTC5b43XX
Jacquie and I are keeping Dean of the House @RepDonYoung in our thoughts as he fights COVID-19 – I don’t know anyone tougher than my friend Don. Hope to see you back on the House Floor soon!

Today I sent a letter to @HHSgov urging @SecAzar to use unallocated Provider Relief Funds to help assisted living facilities procure #PPE for their staff and secure widespread #COVID19 testing for their residents. Read more here ⬇️ https://t.co/Y1eRWEvqDA

Our #seniors have been impacted the most by the #COVID19 crisis. Almost 80% of COVID-19 deaths occur in people 65 and over and those in assisted living facilities are at even higher risk. https://t.co/pXxg9PXexl

Incredible news! Pfizer & @HHSgov are working together to bring us a vaccine to #COVID19 & thanks to #OperationWarpSpeed 100 million doses of the vaccine will be distributed! #medicalinnovation https://t.co/lHxFugAvad

Health care providers—especially small & rural hospitals—have been fighting on the front lines of the #COVID19 crisis. They need sustained relief not new onerous reporting requirements. https://t.co/Ptdg9pIw3a

Keeping #seniors safe from the spread of #COVID19 is a top priority - but combatting the often-debilitating effects of loneliness should be as well. Finally our state is allowing Minnesotans to visit their families in nursing homes! https://t.co/wqeuFUEAuk

Our mental health requires constant maintenance and care especially during the #COVID19 crisis. This #WorldMentalHealthDay take a moment to check in on your mental health. More via @SCTimes: https://t.co/v1f7CWLJ8F

Attention MN #Veterans: VA Under Secretary for Benefits Dr. Paul R. Lawrence PhD will be hosting a tele-town hall TOMORROW for MN Vets & their families:  - Oct. 6 at 5pm(ET)/4pm(CT) . - Call-In: 833-380-0417  The call will be focused on #COVID19 & benefit program updates

Today I was tested for COVID-19 by the Office of the Attending Physician. I was informed that my test results are negative. I am not exhibiting symptoms and will continue to follow the recommended guidelines issued by the Attending Physician. Read more: https://t.co/STwCPq4RYS https://t.co/aPExMIuiEV

Our teachers have been going above and beyond to adapt to educating during the #COVID19 crisis and for many of them that means paying for their classroom’s #PPE out of their own pockets. https://t.co/yZWGHTAsQI
Another opportunity to get much needed relief from the impact of the #coronavirus outbreak. Learn more here: https://t.co/0bOY5R37bg

I’ve fought in Congress to keep our #smallbusiness community a cornerstone of our #COVID19 relief with programs like the #PaycheckProtectionProgram which supported more than 51 million American jobs. #SWB2020

This year small businesses have been challenged like never before. They’ve served as essential hubs for communities across our country all while facing closures and navigating the #COVID19 Crisis. #SWB2020 https://t.co/qWWgxz3Aaw

Thanks to @DCGKNasim for taking the time to talk to me this week! Minnesotans in the Northwest Angle depend on passage across the Canadian border and #COVID19 has brought the border and local business to a halt. We will find a solution!

Our farmers & producers have been hard at work keeping our food supply strong through the COVID-19 crisis but many are struggling to make ends meet. To support them through the pandemic @USDAFSA launched the Coronavirus Food Assistance Program (#CFAP)
FINAL REMINDER: Tomorrow is the last day to apply for @USDA’s Coronavirus Food Assistance Program. Learn more about how to apply via my website: https://t.co/MDWa5EedxL https://t.co/wlYDQGy1Mx

REMINDER: Applications for @USDA’s Coronavirus Food Assistance Program (#CFAP) close FRIDAY Sept. 11. Learn how to apply via my website: https://t.co/MDWa5EedxL https://t.co/C6fAPJJ8dm
The #COVID19 crisis has brought many challenges—one of the largest among them is how to prevent social disconnection and its effects while keeping vulnerable populations safe.
Incredible - @EPA has approved the use of a new product which will kill #COVID19 on surfaces for up to a week! https://t.co/DjmqmQQ6uD
.@WashingtonCoMN Residents—if your income has been impacted by #COVID19 & you are now struggling with rent & utility payments you may be eligible for support under the #CARES Act.

#CommunityHealthCenters are an essential piece of our public health response to crises like #COVID19 serving nearly 29 million Americans every year.

Thank you to Acting @DeptVetAffairs Dep. Sec. Pamela Powers for coming to the St. Cloud VA this week! Glad to have time to discuss how the #VA and congress can support vets in the #COVID19 crisis & beyond.

The #COVID19 crisis has hit our small businesses hard but I’m proud to see Minnesotans stepping up for their community. Thank you to Sherburne County on this effort to provide additional relief!  https://t.co/5SdMKzeb3V
The #COVID19 crisis has put stress on many Americans' finances. Thanks to @EdwardJones for including me in your roundtable on how we can get Americans the support they need! https://t.co/HR8lPdjnoL

#Telehealth has been an incredible weapon in our fight against #COVID19 but it remains out of reach for too many of our rural communities. Thank you to @RealDonaldTrump and @SeemaCMS for this order to improve rural telehealth access! https://t.co/yyfU2UZw1f

Have you gotten robocalls text messages or emails offering free face masks free COVID-19 testing kits or treatments? Don’t let scammers use the #COVID19 crisis to steal your #Medicare info. Learn more here: https://t.co/0b3U8Dfw07

Proud to see small breweries & taprooms thriving esp. after being hit hard by the #COVID19 crisis. Last month I sent a letter to @RepKevinBrady & @RepRichardNeal to advocate for this important industry! https://t.co/VIPSbgRx3j

They’ve been working overtime and this outbreak has hit local radio & television stations hard. I sent a letter with my #BroadcastersCaucus co-chair @RepBrendanBoyle to House &Senate leadership in support of local broadcaster assistance in #COVID19Relief  https://t.co/pDPLDCbK2r https://t.co/0RIagrmdXy

Reliable accessible child care supports our frontline workers and will help get our nation back to work. Great to meet with @SIFMA this week to talk about how we can support the future of capital markets as we recover from #COVID19.

The COVID-19 crisis has resulted in many new relief programs designed to help Minnesotans farms small businesses and more. Unfortunately trying to navigate these programs can be difficult. My casework team stands ready to help. Learn more here: https://t.co/PwsvmjIJW2

ICYMI: I Joined Jay Caldwell on @WJON_News to discuss the pressing issues our communities are facing. We covered my new legislation the Community OutPost (COP) Outreach and Engagement Act and the ongoing fight to defeat Coronavirus. Listen here: https://t.co/6siS3VbF7W

Met w. Dr. Greg Schoen at the @FairviewHealth in Princeton to discuss how we can defeat the #COVID19 virus. My office was able to connect Fairview with thousands of masks for frontline health care workers and I was honored to visit and see the outstanding care they provide. https://t.co/nAbMpZiGZK

During this #COVID19 crisis being confined to your home was more difficult for some more than others. I was proud to meet with @nnedv to learn how we can work together to #enddomesticviolence and make home a safe place for all of us.
Proud to see concrete signs of recovery during our unprecedented #COVID19 crisis. Americans are eager to get back to work! https://t.co/UUk0Yt1T5X

As we address the economic fallout from #COVID19 it’s important that we continue to prioritize a plan to stem our growing national debt. I am a cosponsor of my colleague @RepJohnCurtis’s #DealwithDebtTodayAct to keep Congress accountable. Read more here: https://t.co/SsgYj6ONFa

Glad to see @RepBlaine is set to serve on the Select Subcommittee on the Coronavirus Crisis. I know he will ensure the focus of this group of legislators remains on the facts about our nation’s quick and effective response to #COVID19.
Jacquie and I have continued to pray for comfort and healing for everyone impacted by #COVID19. #NationalDayofPrayer
